@node "e_History" "History"

@{u}History (Programmgeschichte)@{uu}

20.8.95 - first Aminet release V1.0

 3.9.95 - fixed problems with color remapping
          now the images are displayed in their correct colours on
          all promoted screens (even the Foozle screen)

 9.1.96 - latest release V1.2
          the images can be sorted into subdirectories
          new commodity interface and GUI, preferences can be saved
          the window now has a 3D border and a hidden sizing gadget
          the window can be resized, images will be scaled
          implemented a title image and an image for unknown users

@endnode


@node "e_Bilder" "Images"

@{u}How to expand my picture database?@{uu}

New images will be available via AmiNet (in case we will receive enough) and directly at Flowerpower's BBS (2:2480/465, Tel. +49-89-8949235). We hereby want to encourage every ThumbMail user to send us his picture (-> see @{"IMPORTANT" link "e_Bilder_an_uns" 0})

Filerequest: ThumbMail.lzx - contains main program and some portraits
             (LZX ist requestable as "LZX", everybody should own it!)

             ThumbMails_update.lzx - for the latest portraits
                                     (send us your portrait! -> see @{"IMPORTANT" link "e_Bilder_an_uns"})

High resolution images of many users of the german AMIGA.GER (FidoNet) are available from Ingo Jürgensmann (2:2449/413.19) who has addicted himself to collect and archive these pictures.

@endnode


@node "e_Shareware" "Shareware"

@{u}This program is Shareware. What does that mean?@{uu}

Everybody who regularly uses this program, should pay a little sum of money to the authors. This currently makes up 10 german marks (or $10, A$ 10, AS 80 or any sum of money in your currency that equals DM 15). This is really not much and does surely not make us Dagobert Duck.

But you thereby support the development of the program and you encourage us to implement many many fucking marvellous features. We are students and can really make use of any support.

You can send us the money e.g. in an envelope (with some thick paper for protection against sneaking), send us an EuroCheque, you can use an international money order or directly transfer it to our bank account. (No foreign cheques or international bank transfers)

@{u}Donation account:@{uu} 49573 at Raiffeisenbank Germering-Olching eG (bank ID: 70169380), Germany

@endnode


